{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"de2b115f-8313-4039-a6bf-901eeb3af7f9","content":"To migrate your NUnit project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. **Replace packages** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove these -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"4.6.0\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add these -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"5.0.0\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.5.3\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable the platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **5.0+** has built-in Microsoft.Testing.Platform support (no separate runner package needed).\n- You no longer need `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`; replace it with `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses the new platform instead of VSTest.\n- Your existing `[Test]`, `[TestCase]`, etc. attributes remain unchanged.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0a4de245-2488-434f-a42c-b53fe51c589b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest (using NUnit3TestAdapter 4.6.0 and Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing migration - I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search files.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":438,"requestId":"7C2A:29C906:2598B9A:299C9A0:69F93E1A"},"id":"cea20481-0982-403e-888c-a2a1fd2b1bf9","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:30.349Z","parentId":"7ebb7c96-3a68-44ba-b6ef-14afb27a1296"}
